Poetry - Adding Dependencies

Manage dependencies in your Python project with [bold]poetry[/bold]. Use the [bold]add[/bold] subcommand to add new dependencies.

[dim]# Adding dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow]

[dim]# Adding dependencies to a group[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add[/bold] [yellow]--group=GROUP_NAME[/yellow] [cyan]package_name[/cyan]

[dim]# Package Sources[/dim]

- A [bold]name[/bold], with an optional constraint ([cyan]requests[/cyan], [cyan]requests@^2.3.0[/cyan])
- A [bold]git repository[/bold] ([cyan]git+ssh://...[/cyan], [cyan]git+https://...[/cyan])
- A [bold]revision[/bold] of a git repository ([cyan]git+ss://...#refspec[/cyan])
- A [bold]wheel[/bold] ([cyan]my-package.whl[/cyan])
- A [bold]directory[/bold] ([cyan]my-package/[/cyan],
- A [bold]tarball[/bold] ([cyan]https://.../my-package.tar.gz[/cyan],)
